# FILE:        moos-ivp-cicd-testing/README
# DESCRIPTION: Overview of the MOOS-IvP CI/CD testing workspace
##############################################################################

Introduction
============
This repository is a small MOOS-IvP CI/CD testing workspace for fast,
self-evaluating mission runs.

Main Contents
=============
missions/first_draft
  Fast obstacle-avoidance baseline mission for pAutoPoke, pMissionEval,
  and uMayFinish.

missions/cmgr_smoke
  Fast pContactMgrV20 stem mission. The default evaluation is timer-driven
  and contact-focused rather than arrival-driven.

missions/cmgr_multi
  Fast multi-contact pContactMgrV20 stem mission. The default evaluation is
  timer-driven and checks both two-contact counting and closest-contact
  selection.

harnesses/H01-cmgr_smoke
  nspatch harness over missions/cmgr_smoke for a 14-case contact-manager
  regression matrix.

harnesses/H02-cmgr_multi
  nspatch harness over missions/cmgr_multi for an 8-case multi-contact
  regression matrix.

src
  Legacy example code from the original template that still builds in this
  repository.

Build
=====
  ./build.sh

Typical Runs
============
  cd missions/first_draft
  ./zlaunch.sh 10

  cd ../cmgr_smoke
  ./zlaunch.sh 10

  cd ../../harnesses/H01-cmgr_smoke
  ./zlaunch.sh 10
  ./zlaunch.sh --just_make 10

  cd ../H02-cmgr_multi
  ./zlaunch.sh 10
  ./zlaunch.sh --case=count_two_pass 10

Running zlaunch.sh
==================
In a mission directory such as missions/cmgr_smoke, ./zlaunch.sh now performs
one short headless mission run by default. It cleans local artifacts, launches
through the shared xlaunch.sh path, lets pAutoPoke deploy, lets pMissionEval
grade, and lets uMayFinish stop the run once evaluation is complete.

In the harness directory harnesses/H01-cmgr_smoke, ./zlaunch.sh runs the whole
contact-manager matrix by default. It applies nspatch overlays case-by-case,
runs the stem mission once per case through shared xlaunch.sh, reads the
mission results, and appends one summary line per case to the harness
results.txt file. It also backs up and restores any pre-existing meta_*.moosx
or meta_*.bhvx files in the stem mission. Use:

  ./zlaunch.sh --case=detect_baseline_pass 10

to run one case only.

For the detailed patching flow, see harnesses/H01-cmgr_smoke/NSPATCH.md.
For the multi-contact patching flow, see harnesses/H02-cmgr_multi/NSPATCH.md.

Results Files
=============
After harness runs there are stem-local and harness-local results files:

missions/cmgr_smoke/results.txt
  One line from the most recent mission run.

missions/cmgr_multi/results.txt
  One line from the most recent multi-contact mission run.

harnesses/H01-cmgr_smoke/results.txt
  One line per harness case, including expected vs actual.

harnesses/H02-cmgr_multi/results.txt
  One line per multi-contact harness case, including expected vs actual.

Typical mission result line:

  form=cmgr_harness  mmod=detect_edge_pass  grade=pass  eval=true
  seen=true  closest=intruder  range=14  mhash=[MILD-ROWE]

Field meanings:

form
  The mission family or harness family name.

mmod
  The specific case or mission variant.

grade
  The pass/fail result decided by pMissionEval.

eval
  Whether the timer-driven evaluation checkpoint was reached.

seen
  Whether pContactMgrV20 posted CONTACT_SEEN=true by the checkpoint.

closest
  The contact name reported in CONTACT_CLOSEST.

range
  The CONTACT_CLOSEST_RANGE value at evaluation time.

mhash
  The short mission hash for the generated mission files.

Typical harness summary line:

  case=detect_edge_pass  expected=pass  actual=pass  status=ok
  form=cmgr_harness  mmod=detect_edge_pass  grade=pass  eval=true
  seen=true  closest=intruder  range=14  mhash=[MILD-ROWE]

Extra harness-only fields:

case
  The harness case name.

expected
  What the harness expected the mission to grade.

actual
  What the mission actually graded.

status
  ok if expected matches actual, otherwise mismatch.

Some optional fields such as count and list appear only on the cases that are
actually testing those published variables.

For the multi-contact stem, count is the number of alerted contacts while list
is the known-contact list still tracked by contact manager.

For the current contact-manager matrix, every case is expected to end with
mission grade=pass. Negative cases are intentionally written this way: they
pass when the mission correctly confirms non-detection or another expected
absence.

grade and actual are both shown because they come from different layers:

grade
  The mission's own result from pMissionEval.

actual
  The harness's extracted view of that mission result for comparison against
  expected.

Notes
=====
- Missions are intended to auto-deploy, self-evaluate, write results.txt,
  and exit cleanly.
- The contact-manager harness patches pMissionEval per case so each mission
  run behaves more like a unit test expressed as a short mission.
- The current H01-cmgr_smoke suite contains 14 cases and validated at about
  143 seconds wall clock on March 18, 2026 at warp 10.
- The current H02-cmgr_multi suite contains 8 cases and validated at about
  83 seconds wall clock on March 18, 2026 at warp 10.
- Most of that wall-clock cost is launch and teardown overhead rather than
  mission runtime.

